            <div type="commentary">
                 <p>The inscription contains the common formula words MAQQI 'son' and KOI. According to McManus (1991, 119) <q>KOI, which is invariably written with the first supplementary character (the X-forfid) and is alone among formula words in not being attested later, has been explained as a word defining locality, <q>here</q>, analogous to HIC IACIT in the British inscription</q>.</p>
            </div>
